<br>
I am looking for some advice from more experienced players.  I am just now reaching the level where I can participate in plane and dragon raids (47 now) and am looking forward to it immensely.<br>
<br>
The first raid I will attend is in Hate (I loved the idea of being initiated on Phread’s raid).  My thought is to attend at least three (maybe four our five) raids to learn how to work effectively in large multi-group settings, and to learn the plane, mobs, strategies, etc.  After that, I wanted to try the same number of raids in Fear.  <br>
<br>
However, I’ve seen some posts about players who only attend raids in planes where “their” armor drops, and that they are perceived as greedy or self-centered.  I know Hate has a number of enchanter items, but I would rather learn one area and learn it well before trying another plane.  Will this give others the perception that I’m only focusing on the plane where enchanter armor drops?  I know Fear has cryosilk, which is designed for intelligence casters, so don’t know if that makes a difference.<br>
<br>
Let me know your thoughts.  If I will damage my reputation by focusing on one plane until I am operating at peak efficiency, then I would rather go ahead and try to learn two planes at once.  Thank you for your feedback!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umukhtaribnasim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukhtar Ibn Asim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/7/01 12:50:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for advice</span><hr size=1> /shrug<br>
<br>
It doesn't really make a difference which plane you go to to &quot;learn how to raid.&quot;  Both are pretty much identical in terms of mob levels and strategies employed by the raids.  The only only real differences are those of flavors...<br>
<br>
Hate = run to break location, camp, then come back and pull patrols that path nearby<br>
Hate = 2 floors = AE spells aggro stuff on 2nd floor = don't use AE spells<br>
Hate = smaller aggro radius + lots of buildings to block line of sight<br>
Hate = lots of gem drops<br>
Fear = run to break location and immediately fight patrols that swoop through the camp regularly<br>
Fear = single level = AE spells ok<br>
Fear = crazy, insane aggro from seemingly beyond visual range + little to block line of sight<br>
Fear = not many enchanter drops i.e. big bonus points in the oppinion polls<br>
Fear = low gem drops<br>
<br>
<br>
I've been on about 4 raids in each plane now.  And honestly I could probably lead a raid in either at this point.  /shrug I don't think going to 4 or 5 hate raids would give you a &quot;reputation.&quot;  But at the same time I don't see any really need to limit yourself to Hate in order to learn about raiding.  IMO Fear can be a pretty good training ground for getting people to follow instructions as the break in is much less forgiving.<br>
<br>
 <p>
