Vita Infinita</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udaeon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/7/01 2:49:08 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/hamster2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for advice</span><hr size=1> I too, did Fear about 4 times before going to Hate.  Hell, I had a lot more Fear than Hate raids for a loooong time, although it's finally flipped over to about 18 Hate and 15 Fear.. <br>
<br>
I personally find Fear *insanely* dull after the break.  All pulls are routine, hardly ever any adds, and usually only 3 or 4 mobs at the most.  The only exception to that besides the break would be the Temple, if you're lucky enough to have it pulled.<br>
<br>
Hate I like.  In Hate, there can be wandering adds.  Pathing in Hate is absolutely horrible, and sometimes you'll get 8 mobs charging your raid.  Am I a bit of a masochist?  I guess, but that's the kinda stuff that makes this game all the more worthwhile for me - The stuff that gets your heart pounding, your mind blasting, and leaves you with a real sense of accomplishment - something I think is unique (not that other classes don't feel this way - I just mean, in the sense that, "Hey, I can't believe I kept that under control and lived to tell about it") to the enchanter class and one of the biggest reasons I'm so happy I chose it.  <br>
<br>
I've had some absolutely epic battles in Hate, but I don't mean to turn you off Fear.  You learn a LOT, very FAST by going to either plane.  Probably one of the most important lessons you'll learn right away is not to be afraid to get HIT.  Because some of that stuff hits HARD and FAST and it takes nerves of steel to stand there trying to mez/stun/control it in some way without running crying like a little baby for someone to get it off you.<br>
<br>
So... go to both planes.  Watch, learn, and LISTEN (key advice for a raid) and I gurantee you will learn an incredible amount in only a few raids. <p><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
